{
  "stem": "3040.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I cherish these pictures because I remember, if you would look at this picture, he is-- it was like you like a baby Moses.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was not just a learned man, but a very dedicated, selfless person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And as I said, we had the opportunity to, to talk one on one in his study.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I was very much influenced him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But still, I, I come from a family of six, and I'm the oldest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when at about 14 years of age, I became very much interested in secular learning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was reading books which this rabbi probably wouldn't want me to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But you cannot go against nature.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And of course, in that way, I was the only one in my family who turned secular.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And all the others-- my two brothers and sisters, of which pictures you will see later, are still presenting themselves as the Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They're wearing different garb, and they are bearded and all this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I'm the only one who-- maybe in their minds, maybe I was an outcast at this time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But this is-- this is how it was with me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were a large number of major synagogues, like the Alta shul, the Remuh shul, the Kupa shul, the Hoykh shul.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And these were major synagogues.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But besides that, there were small synagogues and shtiebel, mostly congregated by, by certain groups of people, mostly Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because I would say of the 60,000 Jews in Krakow, there are probably 90% were Hasidim, and only maybe 10% were secular.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in fact, you didn't see a Jewish store open on a Saturday, even by, by the non-Hasidim because they were so influenced by the culture.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So everybody was for the-- for the appearance was a shomer Shabbas actually.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
